args:
After the Windwyrm Midgardsormr saved Zethia
and her allies from danger, she realizes what
must be done and suggests that Ilia form a pact
with Elysium, the Holywyrm. Ilia, however, is
less than fond of the idea.
I am, thanks to all of you.\nI fear I owe you a debt.
WE'RE the ones who owe a debt here!\nWe'd be dead if not for you.
I'm sorry we had to hurt other dragons,\nbut we had to do something.
I understand—though can scarce believe\nour reunion after all this time should take\nsuch form as this.
Still, I am glad everyone is all right.
(This dragon shares both name and mana\nwith the Mistholt's Windwyrm...)
(This can be no mere coincidence—\nbut what does fate have in store for us?)
Meene? Ilia? You know this dragon?
Yes, we faeries and dragons have\nsome interaction with each other.
Midgardsormr has kept an eye on me since\nI was but a little spriteling, and continued\nto do so even when I left our kingdom.
He's like my big brother.\n...My VERY big brother.
Yeah, and he's sort of like an uncle\nto me, I guess. Ol' Uncle Mids!
Then you do not view humans as an enemy\neven though you are a dragon?
He is one of a small number among the\ndragons in a neutral faction.
Humanity and the dragons are not meant\nto war with one another like this.
I had thought there must be a way for\nus to form new bonds and move forward\ntogether, but now...
Yeah... Humans have been acting like\nCOMPLETE jerks lately.
I'm sorry I couldn't stop them,\nMidgardsormr.
You've nothing to apologize for.\nNow, if I may, who are these others?
Ah, right. This is Zethia, and the fellow\nhere is Mordecai.
Quite a curious form the young lady\nhas taken, don't you think?
But the man... He is from another world.
That's right. I summoned him here.
I know we dragons and faeries find the\nidea of beings from other worlds living\nin our own to be unthinkable.
But Ilia is human, and I cannot force\nour sense of things upon her.
But you know our dragon friend's beliefs,\nyes? And what sort of calamity might\nensue when he learns of this?
Even so, I want to respect Ilia's decisions.
Meaning you are suitably prepared.\n...And are you, Ilia?
Of course! I've been prepared since I\nstarted my research on the omega keys.
And once I met Mordecai,\nmy resolve got even stronger.
Then I will trust in said resolve.
That was a REALLY long night.
For now, it would be best to rest.\nWe can consider our next move once\nheads are clear and bodies repaired.
Yes. There's things we need to inform\nMidgardsormr about, too.
Indeed. But rest now, my friends;\nI shall stand the watch.
I closed my eyes, but couldn't fall asleep.
In history, the summoning of the Other served\nas the catalyst for humans and dragons to\nfinally set their differences aside.
But there IS no Other in this world. Still,\nhaving said that, I do not think summoning\nthe Other now is the correct answer.

However, if things continue as they are, either
humans or dragons are going to be destroyed.
There can be no future for them if they do not
travel the path of kinship and camaraderie.
It was the first Auspex Ilia and the Holywyrm\nElysium who forged a path to the future—\nand those two alone.
And there is no one who can inform them\nof that except me, who knows the future.
Perhaps this is the reason I was sent here?
All right, time to make a plan.
Actually, I need to say something first.
Oh dear. You look rather grim.
Does it have to do with the future?
The future? What does that mean?
I come from a world a thousand years\nin the future.
I cannot fathom how I came here, nor why.
I simply woke up in this place. My body,\nhowever, is still in my original world,\nwhich is why I am a mana projection.
It is, actually.\nThe future is just another world.
Might someone please try to explain this\nto me in simpler terms?
Think of it like this: If we hadn't run to\nthe capital last night, today would have\nbeen an entirely different morning, right?
Essentially, it would be another world.
There are many worlds besides this one,\nand they all influence each other.

Which means there's a world in the future
where those branches have continued for
a thousand years—and that's where Zethia
has come from.
I both do and do not understand.
A thousand years from now, dragons and\nhumans walk alongside one another on a\npath of kinship.
But this world has diverged from the\nhistory I know, and now the two species\nthreaten to tear each other apart.
I have been wavering as to what I should\ndo, but I know I cannot continue like this.

I want to fix this world and bring it closer
to the history I know. In doing so, I hope it
can arrive at a future where humans and
dragons are able to live together in peace.
Supposing the tidings you bring are true,\nwhat means do you propose to accomplish\nthis goal of yours?
As things stand, the two races are in the\nthrall of mutual hatred. What can be done?
I'm going to tell you everything there is\nabout the history that I know...
...Wait, I form a PACT with Elysium?!
You claim an era will arrive in which\npeople and dragons form pacts?
The pact between Ilia and the Holywyrm\nis the origin of all pacts made between\npeople and dragons.
And a crystal called the Primal Pactstone\nserved as proof of said pacts.
This stone was long protected\nby the Ilian Church.
Its light shone upon and mingled with\na hero who respected the dragons\nand became of dragonblood.
And your people are the ones who've\ninherited this dragonblood?
Okay, I think I pretty much understand.\nSo you say I'm supposed to go make a\npact thingie with Elysium, yeah?
Sorta weird to think of the two of us\nguiding everybody...
Though there be no Other in this world,\nI am still certain you and Elysium can\nguide all in it to a brighter future.
And if you did so, that would end the war.\nAn era of peace would be upon us\nwithout overlarge changes in history.
Now, you must forge the pact, transcend\nthe boundaries of species, and join as one.
...I'm sorry, Zethia. But I can't do that.
But that is the only hope!
I'm afraid the Holywyrm doesn't see things\nthe way you do.
Yep. Not that it was my idea.
The Holywyrm wishes to forge a pact\nwith Ilia, and has desired so all along.
However, the pact the Holywyrm seeks\nis no shared bond between human and\ndragon such as the one you spoke of.
A pact that isn't a bond?\nI don't understand!
